# Configurable Branding

Saral v1.0 App supports configurable branding feature. As this application will be used by different states , this feature will avoid maintaining different frontend source code to customise color themese and logs displayed.

Logo and theme colors can be customised by using below REST APIs. To understand more on these APIs , refer swagger documentation.

```
GET  /brand
GET  /brand/default
```

Refer sample brand json returned by `GET /brand` API below. If entry without state value is configured in backend , it will be used as default theme and logo.

```
{
    "appName": "Saral OCR App",
    "themeColor1": "#D72819",
    "themeColor2": "#FBE9E7",
    "logoImage": ""
}
```

From `v1.5.0` release screen customizations are supported using brand APIs. `screenLabels` is optional element which can be populated if screens of app needs to be customised. Keys under `screenLabels`are fixed as per Saral App screens, but values can be changed based on what needs to be displayed.

Sample for `screenLabels` customisation.
